  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, a dataset like Banking with 77 classes shows the biggest performance gap.",
    "Decoder-only models do not have specific layers in the architecture to model all the possible intents but need to remember the list passed in the prompt in the training data.",
    "For few-shot approaches, the presence of this enumeration of possible intents in the prompt is the only information the model has to produce the right answer.",
    "We observe that decoder-only models struggle to retain a long list of intents and produce the right answer.",
    "Fine-tuned encoderonly models are less sensitive to the number of classes because they are encoded as part of the classification layers.The fine-tuned LLaMA2 exhibits class imbalance impact, particularly when minority classes closely resemble the majority class."
  ],
